ffmpeg's nvenc version is more up-to-date and closer to the Nvenc spec,
libav's version is sort of outdated.

While performing this more 'academic' task, it seems that the overall
ffmpeg code is in much better shape, i.e. re-factored code, more modularized,
better error handling. The worst seems to be for libav that contributors
often simply copy/paste ffmpeg patches against it (like this here),
where incompatibilities may exist and therefor bugs beign introduced.

